---
import Layout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Ensemble Coaching | Ted's Voice Academy" 
  description="Vocal and performance coaching for choirs, quartets, and vocal groups. Build unity, tuning, and expressive sound with Ted's Voice Academy."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Ensemble Coaching</span>
      <h1>Find your voice together</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Vocal and performance coaching for groups seeking unity, efficiency, and expressive sound.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro Section -->
  <section class="intro-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <p class="intro-text">
        Strong ensemble singing starts with strong individual skills — and with a shared understanding of how voices work together. I help choirs/choruses, quartets, and other vocal groups develop tuning, unity, and authentic performance presence.
      </p>
      <p class="intro-text">
        Whether you're preparing for competition, working through a specific challenge, or simply want to connect more deeply as an ensemble, I can help your group find its voice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who I Work With Section -->
  <section class="who-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Groups of all kinds</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">I work with ensembles across traditions and contexts. Here's a sampling of the groups I coach:</p>
      
      <div class="cards-grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Church choirs</h3>
          <p>From small worship teams to full sanctuary choirs, I help church musicians develop their sound and lead their congregations with confidence.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Barbershop quartets and choruses</h3>
          <p>I've spent decades in the barbershop world as a performer, director, and coach. I understand what judges listen for and how to help groups achieve ring, unity, and emotional connection.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
          <h3>A cappella groups</h3>
          <p>Whether you're a college ensemble, community group, or professional vocal band, I can help you tighten your sound and elevate your performances.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
          <h3>School and youth ensembles</h3>
          <p>I bring nearly 30 years of choral conducting experience in public schools. I know how to meet young singers where they are and help them grow.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Community choirs</h3>
          <p>Singing together builds connection. I help community groups develop their musicianship while keeping the joy at the center.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Competition-focused groups</h3>
          <p>If you're preparing for contest, I can help you refine the details that make the difference — tuning, vowel matching, phrasing, and stage presence.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Help With Section -->
  <section class="help-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What we work on</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Every ensemble has different needs. Here are some of the areas I address:</p>
      
      <div class="help-grid">
        <div class="help-item">
          <h3>Tuning and intonation</h3>
          <p>When voices lock in, the sound transforms. I help groups understand the mechanics of tuning and develop the listening skills that make it happen.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-item">
          <h3>Unity and vowel matching</h3>
          <p>A unified sound isn't about erasing individuality. It's about making intentional choices together. We work on vowel shapes, tone color, and the subtle adjustments that create a cohesive ensemble sound.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-item">
          <h3>Performance presence</h3>
          <p>Great singing deserves great delivery. I help groups connect with their audience, tell the story, and bring genuine emotion to the stage.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-item">
          <h3>Section development</h3>
          <p>Sometimes the work happens in smaller groups. I coach section leaders and help individual voice parts strengthen their foundation.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="help-item">
          <h3>Director support</h3>
          <p>I work alongside directors to address specific challenges, prepare for performances, or bring a fresh perspective to repertoire.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="how-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>How ensemble coaching works</h2>
      
      <div class="how-content">
        <div class="how-block">
          <h3>The first step</h3>
          <p>We start with a conversation about your group's goals. Tell me what you're working toward, and I'll share how I might help.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="how-block">
          <h3>Flexible formats</h3>
          <p>I design each engagement around what your ensemble needs. Options include:</p>
          <ul class="format-list">
            <li><strong>One-time workshops</strong> — A focused session on a specific skill or piece of repertoire</li>
            <li><strong>Ongoing coaching</strong> — Regular sessions over weeks or months to build skills systematically</li>
            <li><strong>Competition prep</strong> — Intensive work leading up to contest or performance</li>
            <li><strong>Sectional coaching</strong> — Targeted work with individual voice parts</li>
            <li><strong>Custom workshops</strong> — Sessions designed around your group's specific goals</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="how-block">
          <h3>Location</h3>
          <p>I can work with your group at your rehearsal space, or smaller ensembles can come to my studio in Lacey, Washington. Virtual coaching is also available for certain types of work.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to Expect Section -->
  <section class="expect-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>What to expect</h2>
      
      <p>I approach ensemble coaching the same way I approach individual instruction: expression first, technique in service of expression.</p>
      
      <p>We'll work on the physical and musical foundations that let voices come together freely — breath support, resonance, vowel placement, and listening skills. We'll also explore the performance side — how to connect with each other and with your audience, how to tell the story, and how to bring your authentic selves to the music.</p>
      
      <p>I explain the "why" behind what we're doing. When your singers understand how their voices work, they can keep growing on their own. That's the goal.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to elevate your ensemble?</h2>
      <p>The first step is a conversation. Tell me about your group and your goals, and I'll share how I can help.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get in Touch</a>
      <p class="cta-secondary">Questions? Reach out anytime: <a href="mailto:ted@tedsvoiceacademy.com">ted@tedsvoiceacademy.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Hero Section */
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy-deep) 0%, var(--color-navy-medium) 100%);
    padding: 5rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw + 1rem, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    max-width: 650px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  /* Buttons */
  .btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    border: none;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--color-gold-bright);
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--color-gold-hover);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(212, 168, 75, 0.3);
  }

  /* Container Narrow */
  .container-narrow {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Intro Section */
  .intro-section {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .intro-text {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .intro-text:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Who Section */
  .who-section {
    background: var(--color-white);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .who-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw + 1rem, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .section-intro {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
  }

  .cards-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold-bright);
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .card p {
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Help Section */
  .help-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy-deep) 0%, var(--color-navy-medium) 100%);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .help-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw + 1rem, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-white);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .help-section .section-intro {
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .help-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .help-item {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .help-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .help-item p {
    color: var(--color-cream);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* How Section */
  .how-section {
    background: var(--color-off-white);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .how-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw + 1rem, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  .how-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .how-block h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .how-block p {
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .format-list {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .format-list li {
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .format-list strong {
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
  }

  /* Expect Section */
  .expect-section {
    background: var(--color-white);
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  .expect-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw + 1rem, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy-deep);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .expect-section p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .expect-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* CTA Section */
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-navy-deep) 0%, var(--color-navy-medium) 100%);
    padding: 4rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw + 1rem, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .cta-section > .container > p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-cream);
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  .cta-secondary {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-cream);
  }

  .cta-secondary a {
    color: var(--color-gold-bright);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .cta-secondary a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* Mobile Adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 3.5rem 0 3rem;
    }

    .intro-section,
    .who-section,
    .help-section,
    .how-section,
    .expect-section,
    .cta-section {
      padding: 3rem 0;
    }

    .cards-grid,
    .help-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
